# Sync README from PROJECT.md

`DukeNukem3DJs/PROJECT.md` is the source of truth for product / port docs.

Whenever you create, edit, or update `PROJECT.md`:

1. Copy its **full** contents into `DukeNukem3DJs/README.md`
2. Copy the same contents into the repo-root `README.md` (`../README.md` from DukeNukem3DJs)
3. On each README only, keep/restore a short top banner that says it is a mirror of `PROJECT.md` and must be updated in the same change
4. Do this in the **same** turn / change set — never leave PROJECT.md and README out of sync

Do not maintain separate README content. Do not summarize PROJECT.md into a shorter README unless the user explicitly asks for a different README style.
